    "type": "flashcard",
    "items": [
      {
        "front": "What is 2 + 3?",
        "back": "2 + 3 = 5. If you have 2 apples and get 3 more, you have 5 apples total.",
        "hint": "Count on your fingers"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 5 + 4?",
        "back": "5 + 4 = 9. Addition means putting groups together to find how many in total.",
        "hint": "Put them together"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 7 - 2?",
        "back": "7 - 2 = 5. If you have 7 cookies and eat 2, you have 5 left.",
        "hint": "Take away some"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 10 - 3?",
        "back": "10 - 3 = 7. Subtraction means taking away from a group.",
        "hint": "Count backwards"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 1 + 1?",
        "back": "1 + 1 = 2. When you add one thing to another thing, you get two things.",
        "hint": "The first addition"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 6 + 4?",
        "back": "6 + 4 = 10. We can skip count: 6...7, 8, 9, 10!",
        "hint": "Makes 10"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 9 - 4?",
        "back": "9 - 4 = 5. We can use counting backwards: 9, 8, 7, 6, 5",
        "hint": "Count down 4 steps"
      },
      {
        "front": "What is 8 + 2?",
        "back": "8 + 2 = 10. We skip count 2 more: 8... 9, 10!",
        "hint": "Gets to 10"
      }
    ]
  },
